features: 20 count box of decorative Disney/Pixar Mashup Band-Aid Brand Adhesive Bandages for kids and toddlers to cover and protect minor cuts and scrapes and to deliver daily wound care protection. Perfect for your family's first aid kit
Fun bandages designed with Disney/Pixar Mashup characters from your child's favorite Disney/Pixar movies. These colorful designs make first aid more fun for your child
These Disney/Pixar Mashup bandages are designed to cover and protect minor cuts and scrapes with a nonstick pad that does not stick to the wound

These Band-Aid Brand Adhesive Bandages come in box with an assortment of sizes and fun character designs. They are great for small wounds, suitable for young kids and can bring a smile to their face with exciting graphics

Individually wrapped sterile adhesive bandages protect sensitive wounds from coming into contact with germs and dirt. For best results, apply bandage to clean, dry skin. Change daily, when wet, or more often if needed
body.description: Care for your child's minor cuts and scrapes and bring a smile to their face with Disney/Pixar Mashup Band-Aid Brand Adhesive Bandages. These first aid adhesive bandages for kids and toddlers cover minor cuts and scrapes to deliver daily wound care and healing protection. Perfect for kids and toddlers, these fun bandages feature Disney/Pixar Mashup characters from Toy Story, Finding Nemo, The Incredibles and more to make first aid more fun for your child. As part of your essential first aid supplies, the decorated bandages protect minor wounds from contact with germs and dirt. These sterile kids' bandages come in various sizes and are comfortable to wear thanks to a non-stick pad that won't adhere to the wound. The box contains individually wrapped bandages in assorted sizes. For best results, apply bandage to clean, dry skin. Change daily, when wet, or more often if needed. ©Disney/Pixar

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: About Us Our products have been used by millions—even billions—of people for more than a century, giving BAND-AID Brand an iconic place in American culture. We reached that place through a history of innovation, healing, and caring. And while we’re always looking forward to see what we can do next and how we can help, sometimes it’s good to take a look back and see how far we’ve come. In 1920 Combining two products from Johnson & Johnson—adhesive tape and gauze—Earle Dickson, a cotton buyer, creates a bandage that his wife can apply herself. And the BAND-AID Brand adhesive bandage is invented.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I’m an adult and I keep these in my bag for myself. A couple days ago though, I was out in public when a child fell down and scraped her knee. She started crying, but stopped as soon as I gave her a Toy Story band-aid. As a teacher, I also plan on getting these for my classroom. I try to keep those variety band-aids for all different skin colors, but this is so much easier.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Cute Prints on a Traditional Band-Aid
reviews.reviewText: Just your basic Band-Aids with a fun print design. Obviously these are geared toward kids. I like to get bandages with various prints to keep on hand for my 7 y/o. Let's face it... kids think bandages are a cure-all, so why not keep some fun prints on hand?These Band-Aids are pretty basic. They stick just like I remember and work the same. They're pretty easy to remove, but are easier to take off when your kid is getting washed because the water helps get the Band-Aid off easier.
